The FIFA trophy is in Mexico as part of a tour of various countries before arriving in Russia where the World Cup will be played between June 14 and July 15. Mexico's soccer team has taken part in 15 World Cups and Russia will be it's seventh consecutive competition. Mexico last reached the quarterfinals in 1986, when it was surpassed by Germany. In the first round of the World Cup, Mexico will join Group F along with Germany, Korea and Sweden. The debut of the team will be on June 17 against the Germans. --Reuters--